= 2021







- Nov. 16, 2021, /*\"Least H^2-norm Updating Quadratic Model for Derivative-free Trust-region Algorithms\"*/ \n
(This is joint work with [http://lsec.cc.ac.cn/~yyx Prof. Ya-xiang Yuan], and presented in the group seminar @LSEC.\n
One can also see [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wC_5tr15Lps Plenary Talk by Prof. Ya-xiang Yuan] in [https://conference.iisertvm.ac.in/bricsmathconf/index.php the 4th BRICS Mathematics Conference.])\n

Prof. Ya-xiang Yuan gave some other talks about this work:\n

[https://www.polyu.edu.hk/en/85anniversary/events/2022/12/1220_least-h2-norm-updating-quadratic-interpolation-model-function/ @ The Hong Kong Polytechnic University], 
[https://news.ustb.edu.cn/info/1087/52176.htm  @ University of Science and Technology Beijing],
[https://math.shu.edu.cn/info/1041/3393.htm  @ 2021年优化理论与方法前沿学术研讨会]



- Shuoran Li, *Pengcheng Xie*, et al., /*\"Simulation of Interaction of Folded Waveguide Space Traveling Wave Tubes with Derivative-free Mixed-integer Based NEWUOA Algorithm\"*/, 2021 7th International Conference on Computer and Communications (ICCC), 2021, pp. 1215-1219, doi: 10.1109/ICCC54389.2021.9674410. [https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/9674410 \[Link\]] \n
(This paper was mainly finished by Shuoran Li, who is an engineer in the 12th Research Institute of [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_Electronics_Technology_Group_Corporation China Electronics Technology Group Corporation], and they coauthored with me since I provided some help about NEWUOA to them. This is definitely an engineering paper, not a mathematical one. Experiments are done by Shuoran Li. :-D )\n

